www.fallenalliance.org/screenshots/downwpst.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: You misunderstood my meaning...</span><hr size=1> saying it is just a triggered spawn is a bit misleading. to do that trigger you have to first camp the shards, get 4 of them, combine them in a box and turn them in. This apparently can only be done by a cleric who has done the ENTIRE quest to this point (no more skipping) /cheer<br>
<br>
Also, thought i have yet to see numbers, the shards are supposed to be very rare, so clerics can camp these for days instead of just rage. Good change, won't change the difficulty much (most of the camps I have done we killed a lot of mobs) but WILL seriously reducing the KSing involved that brought the worst out in so many. Makes it more obtainable by average clerics who can get friends to help camp the mobs. I am willing to bet getting these will be the equivelant of getting 4 Powers of Fire, but instead of soloing the camp, you have to have friends do it with you.<br>
<br>
Comparing the cleric epic and the mage epic is apples to oranges. They provide vastly different benefits in different situations and the quests are entirely different. If you want to compare quests, compare to the warrior quest which also has numerous bottlenecks of anything from farming high in PoA, to camping dragons, to camping semi-rare items; both of these quests provide a reward that is almost exclusively beneficial to the end user (ok, so the warrior epic is generally considered a substantial waste of time to most guilds that can get it, while the Mage epic is actually used by lvl 60 mages in &quot;end game&quot; guilds)<br>
<br>
A lot of the mage epic wasn't well thought out (Quill is just the height of stupidity), but the end result, I believe most mages would agree, is well worth it.<br>
<br>
Be well,<br>
