Quillmane sucks.<br>
<br>
I was in South Karanas the other day, and sent out an /ooc asking for help in locating Quillmane.  &quot;If you see Quillmane, please let me know.  I need it for my epic&quot;.  The response was...<br>
<br>
&quot;If I see Quillmane, I'll kill it.  Doesn't it have a lev cloak?  oooh I want that for my ranger.&quot;<br>
&quot;I'll let you buy the MQ for the cloak if I kill Quillmane&quot;<br>
&quot;Quillmane isn't for your epic.  It is for me, so I can sell the MQ to you for your epic.&quot;<br>
<br>
It seems to me that Verant encourages this greed, and encourages multiquesting.<br>
<br>
One of the items bards needed for their epic was sought after by everyone (white dragon scale) until Verant altered the other quest to require a white dragon hide instead.  This, along with the recent change to Ragefire leads me to the following request.<br>
<br>
Everyone seems to want Quillmane's cloak.  Verant, if you're reading this, please make Quillmane triggered and/or have it drop a new item for our epic that nobody else wants.  At least that way we'd be able to offer some incentive for the ranger/druid's to help us track it.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uradiac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaDiaC</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0> at: 9/5/02 3:44:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uithryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ithryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#333333>(9/5/02 6:02:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1363.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Looks like there's going to be a lot more epic clerics n</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 29 hours spent on Quillmane and i have yet to see her. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
As sad as it is, it's usually more productive to raise the money to mq the cloak than it is to camp Quillmane.<br>
<br>
I agree that the Quillmane portion of the quest should be changed, but until they do, I'd prefer killing all the mobs on the 4th floor of ToFS for 10 hours or so instead of camping Quillmane for 29 hours.<br>
<br>
In coin and weapon drops (take at least 4 summoned bags to hold the weapons), you should be able to easily make 500pp per hour on the 4th floor of ToFS with absolutely no fighting over spawns.  Add to that the occasional sorcerous bowl and embalmers skinning knife drops from Cara Omica (which sell for 500pp+ in the bazaar) and you can make the cash to mq the cloak fairly easily.<br>
<br>
You might get lucky and find Quillmane in an hour, or you might have to camp the zone for weeks.  The cloak mqs for 5Kpp on Druzzil Ro.  I felt it was more efficient to raise the cash than to park my ass in SK.<br>
<br>
Good planning Verant...<br>
