<br>
However, there is no doubt that this change makes our epic the hardest one to obtain by far.<br>
<br>
Between me and my husband, we have several characters, all level 60, and 5 of them have epics (cleric, shaman, enchanter, monk and rogue).<br>
<br>
Having gone through the pains &amp; camps for all of those epics, I have no doubt in my mind that the mage epic is nothing short of nuts!<br>
<br>
Let us look at the monk epic for example. There are some very looong camps, such as Raster in Lguk, Targin in Sol B, and the pipes in Chardok and Karnor's Castle. Still, if you put in the time, you are guaranteed to be rewarded. The Raster camp is one green mob you have to kill every few hours, so that is doable while watching TV, cleaning the house, chatting with your friends... long camp, but stress-free. And sooner or later you get your Idol (and Raster drops it everytime). KC, Chardok and Sol B are fun and provide you and your group with exp and loot while waiting for your rare mobs to spawn. Again, once they do spawn, you are guaranteed your drop, as they all drop what you're looking for every single time. And on top of that, you can always MQ any of these pieces with people who were camping these areas and got the drops with no epic-seeking monk in the group.<br>
<br>
Enchanter epic is a bit different, since almost nothing is MQ'able (you need to combine the 4 pieces of the staff before doing your final turn-in), but it is easy as hell, except for a rare drop in Hate and a rare spawn in Fear. The Hate drop is random however, off any one of the Revs (male or female), and as much as I had a hard time and a few Hate trips before I got my piece, I've heard of as many as 5 essences dropping in one single night. Fear is not so much a problem, the Shissar spawns as often as Magi'Ptasa but again ALWAYS has the drop, and is not hard to get to (the mob used to pop only after Cazic died, but Verant made a change that put it on its own timer, making it easy).<br>
<br>
Shaman epic is a laugh, everything is pretty much always up, all you need to do is go around rounding up your pieces, I finished mine long ago and the only fight that required more than 1 group was City of Mist, and with 2 groups it was overkill.<br>
<br>
Rogue epic is no comment lol <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Cleric epic is very easy as well, all the way up to Ragefire which was a pain, but that has been changed in the last patch so....<br>
<br>
This all leads me to believe that ours is the *only* epic that deals with UNREWARDING time-sink camps. And I am speaking of 3 camps really... everything else seems pretty fair.<br>
<br>
1. Quillmane<br>
2. Plane of Sky<br>
3. Plane of Hate<br>
<br>
Ours is a very unique epic in the sense that as far as those 3 pieces are concerned, you may spend weeks, MONTHS putting all of your efforts into them and get nothing to show for it. <br>
<br>
I actually have a druid *and* ranger that I can 2-box with my mage, and after weeks in South Karana, I have only seen Quillmane 4 times and got leggings all of those times... 3 times I had Quill on track and suddenly bam, &quot;you have lost your target&quot;, only to hear from your_local_greedy_tracker_001 that &quot;he did not have the cloak&quot;. If this was a part of the Monk epic, Quillmane would drop the cloak every time, the cloak would be Magician only, and Quill would not be in a green-mobs zone running around with no specific spawn point. Just look at the other classes' epics, this is a fact!<br>
<br>
Plane of Sky is the same thing. Let's say you are in an uber guild (very few people are), with people willing to spend 2 day+ raids in PoA (very unlikely), and you successfully get to Isle 7 and farm it for a while (grats, you are amongst a select few). The crown is still RARE!!! Again, NO REWARD for your effots! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
And Hate... ahhh Hate. It has been said many times before on these boards... to get this staff Magi must be up (rare), he must have the staff (rare), you must be in a good raid that makes it to him (rare), and then win the roll against X number of mages (rare). *You cannot say this about any other epics, Hate alone makes our epic much harder than any other classes'*.<br>
<br>
Sorry about the long post, but in short, without blaming it on other classes (they have nothing to do with Verant's thinking, so we should wish them all luck and be happy they don't have to go through what we go through), mages indeed have an unfair amount of work to do to get their epics. It is an epic, so it must be challenging - but in my opinion, it must also be rewarding, and I know of many mages that gave up before it was over or worst, got their epics and felt relief more than joy. Relief that the pain was over. My mage was my first character and is still the one closest to my heart (even though my other classes are always wanted before my mage), and I honestly don't know if I will ever get her epic -- at this point, I have made the decision that I will not be a slave to Verant's slave-driving tasks that have been put before me, and I sincerely hope they will make adjustments to these 3 pieces of our epic, just as they did with Ragefire for clerics.<br>
<br>
60 Arch Mage<br>
